description.plain:
Natalie La Rose is a Dutch singer and dancer. In 2013, she signed a deal with Flo Rida’s recording group Republic Records.
She has produced a variety of hit songs including Somebody featuring Jeremih and Around the World featuring Fetty Wap

Born: July 12, 1988 (age 29), Amsterdam, Netherlands

description.plain:
Dutch singer Natalie La Rose taps “Don’t Tell Em” hit-maker Jeremih for her debut single “Somebody.”

Inspired by the late, great Whitney Houston’s “I Wanna Dance With Somebody (Who Loves Me)”, the simple, mid-tempo groove boasts a catchy vibe as they two singers connect for a good night out.

Produced by Kuk Harrell & the Futuristics.

Written by Natalie, Flo Rida & Rook Monroe, “Somebody” was released in January 2015. La Rose is readying her debut album for 2015 via Republic Records and IMG.

description.plain: “Around The World,” featuring Fetty Wap, is Natalie La Rose’s follow-up to debut hit Somebody and the second single from her Somebody EP. “Around The World” was written by Savan Kotecha, Ilya, and Rickard Göransson. The single first premiered through radio on June 1, 2015 ahead of its digital release was June 16.
